Colcannon
  --Holly Nilsson

3 lb russet potatoes or baking potatoes, peeled & quartered
1 white onion or 2 leeks
1/2 head green cabbage ~6 c
1/2 c half and half or heavy whipping cream, warmed
1/4 c salted butter + 3 melted tbsp
salt and black pepper to taste

Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add the potatoes and simmer for 12-15 min or until fork-tender. Dice the white onion into 1/2" pieces or slice the white and light green parts of the leeks thinly and rinse well. Cut the cabbage into 1" pieces. Melt 1/4 c of butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Cook the onion or leeks and cabbage in the butter until the onion is translucent and the cabbage is tender. Once the potatoes are cooked, drain them and return them to the warm pot. Mash the potatoes with a potato masher, adding cream and 3 tbsp melted butter. Season with salt and pepper. Gently fold the mashed potatoes, cabbage, and onions together. Top with additional melted butter if desired.


Notes: can add bacon and/or cook in bacon drippings. Can use yukon gold or even replace 1 lb pf potatoes with parsnips.

